3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BingX calculates FTM/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using the premium/discount mechanism. The funding rate is determined by the difference between the perpetual contract price and the spot index, with a dampening factor applied during high volatility. Long positions pay short positions when the rate is positive, with payments automatically settled from account balances. BingX caps extreme funding rates at ±2% per cycle to prevent excessive costs during market stress."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","FTM","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FTM/USDT on BingX attracts moderate trading volume with funding rates often diverging from major exchanges due to the platform's retail-focused user base. The pair benefits from Fantom's active DeFi ecosystem driving directional sentiment, while BingX's copy trading features can amplify position imbalances that create funding rate premiums."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FTM/USDT funding rates on BingX typically range from -0.3% to +0.5% per 8-hour cycle, with higher volatility during Fantom network updates or DeFi protocol launches. The pair shows pronounced funding spikes during ecosystem developments, often maintaining positive rates for 3-5 consecutive cycles when institutional interest increases. Copy trading activity tends to amplify these trends, as retail traders follow successful strategies, creating sustained directional pressure that keeps funding rates elevated compared to more liquid exchanges."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BingX's retail-focused user base creates regular funding rate disparities with institutional exchanges like Binance or OKX, particularly during Asian trading hours when copy trading activity peaks. Traders can capture spreads of 0.1-0.4% per cycle by taking opposite positions across exchanges, though careful attention to BingX's lower liquidity is essential for execution. The platform's simplified interface attracts directional traders who may hold positions longer than optimal, creating predictable funding rate inefficiencies that sophisticated arbitrageurs can exploit through delta-neutral strategies."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BingX's lower overall liquidity for FTM/USDT creates higher slippage risks during volatile periods, potentially erasing funding rate arbitrage profits if positions require emergency exits. The exchange's focus on copy trading means funding rates can shift rapidly when popular traders change positions, requiring constant monitoring of social sentiment indicators. Additionally, BingX's limited advanced order types may hinder sophisticated risk management strategies, while the platform's relatively smaller insurance fund compared to tier-1 exchanges presents counterparty risks during extreme market stress events."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are FTM/USDT funding rates updated on BingX?","answer":"BingX updates FTM/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. The rates are calculated based on the 1-hour time-weighted average price difference between the perpetual contract and spot index during the hour preceding each settlement."},{"question":"What is the typical funding rate range for FTM/USDT on BingX?","answer":"FTM/USDT funding rates on BingX typically range from -0.3% to +0.5% per 8-hour cycle under normal market conditions. During significant Fantom ecosystem events or broader crypto market volatility, rates can reach the platform's ±2% cap, though such extremes are rare and usually last only 1-2 cycles."},{"question":"Does BingX's copy trading affect FTM/USDT funding rates?","answer":"Yes, BingX's copy trading feature significantly influences FTM/USDT funding rates by amplifying directional positions when popular traders take large positions. This can create sustained funding rate imbalances that last longer than on traditional exchanges, as retail copiers tend to hold positions until the lead trader closes them."},{"question":"What are BingX's trading fees for FTM/USDT perpetuals?","answer":"BingX charges 0.02% maker fees and 0.05% taker fees for FTM/USDT perpetual futures. These fees are competitive within the mid-tier exchange category, though slightly higher than major platforms like Binance or Bybit, which should be factored into funding rate arbitrage calculations."}]}]
